headline: Johnson & Johnson announces first head-to-head study comparing IMAAVY™ with an alternative FcRn blocker in generalized myasthenia gravis (gMG) at AANEM Annual Meeting
summary: Johnson & Johnson (NYSE: JNJ) today announced plans to initiate the first head-to-head study comparing FcRn blockers for patients with generalized myasthenia gravis (gMG), which aims to affirm IMAAVY™ (nipocalimab-aahu) as the FcRn blocker of choice for appropriate gMG patients.
